    Contributing
  </h2>
  <p>
    If you are a HashiCorp staff member, you are eligible to contribute a new
    icon via Figma.
  </p>
  <ol>
    <li>
      <a
        href="https://github.com/hashicorp/flight/issues/new?assignees=&labels=enhancement%2C+triage&template=icon-request.md&title=Flight+Icon+Request%3A+%5Bicon-name%5D"
        class="ds-a"
        rel="external"
      >Open a GitHub issue</a>
      to kick-off work on adding a new icon
    </li>
    <li>
      <ul>
        <li>If you're ready to develop the new icon, create a new branch within
          <a
            href="https://www.figma.com/file/MYiw4kiVpunIMMw0sBkE1t/%E2%9C%8F%EF%B8%8F-Flight-Development?node-id=205%3A0"
            class="ds-a"
            rel="external"
          >Flight Development</a></li>
        <li>You can do this from the Main menu (File > Create branch...)</li>
        <li>Take care to avoid working directly in the default branch!</li>
      </ul>

    </li>
    <li>
      <ul>
        <li>Use the template component in the `Flight Icons - Dev` frame </li>
        <li>Keep your work in this frame, but feel free to create as many
          versions with that template component as you need.</li>
      </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
      <ul>
        <li> Draw your icon glyph using vectors</li>
        <li>Be sure to follow the design guide in the Figma file, taking care to
          follow the conventions around strokes, corner radius and aligning to
          the grid. Try to preserve the ability to edit the glyph where possible
          (avoid flattening).
        </li>
      </ul>

    </li>
    <li>
      <ul>
        <li>When your icon is ready, post to the original GitHub issue to close
          the loop</li>
        <li>The Design Systems team will then add the icon to the grid,
          productionize it, and publish from the
          <a
            href="https://www.figma.com/file/TLnoT5AYQfy3tZ0H68BgOr/Flight-Icons?node-id=164%3A0"
            rel="external"
            class="ds-a"
          >production file</a>.</li>
      </ul>

    </li>
  </ol>
